sublime-jekyll changelog
========================

## v3.1.1 (2016-07-11)

- Close #70 which addresses somewhat recursive exception loop

## v3.1.0 (2016-07-07)

- Close #69 which adds a configurable templates directory path settings key
  named `jekyll_templates_path`.

## v3.0.3 (2016-06-15)

- Close #68 to add more verbose exception messages

## v3.0.2 (2016-02-18)

- Close PR #63
    - Add back `shutil` module removed by #60

## v3.0.1 (2016-02-16)

- Close #59
    - Add send2trash module
    - Update remove_file methods to support send2trash
    - Small bugfixes
- Close #58
    - Add new command for editing `_config.yml` file
- Close #60
    - Remove shutil copy method for settings files
    - Remove duplicate decorators from path methods
- Close #62
    - Add basic path exists check to help with absolute vs. relative paths
- Close #61
    - Fix small typo in documentation

## v3.0.0 (2016-01-31)

* Major Release 3.0.0

- Close #36
- Close #38
- Close #39
- Close #51
- Close #52
    - Deprecate Jekyll syntax files
    - Remove auto-set syntax logic
    - Move open syntax issues to new repo
- Close #53
    - Remove reliance on settings keys (see templates)
- Close #43
    - Create user and project settings migration commands
    - Create backup directory with quick access command
- Close #44
    - Add package debugging
    - Add `jekyll_debug` settings key
- Close #45
    - Add RTFD documentation
- Close #46
    - Add new snippets and completions
- Close #47
    - Move main menu to Tools
    - Add new commands to context menu
- Close #48
    - Add `jekyll_utility_disable` settings key
- Close #49
    - Fix minor formatting bugs in snippets
- Close #50
    - Add ability to create YAML templates
- Remove default keybindings for all platforms


## v2.2.5 (2015-10-18)

- Close #33

## v2.2.4 (2015-03-14)

- Fix #34 (bug with get_setting method)

## v2.2.3 (2015-03-05)

- Close #31
    - Remove date from draft file name
    - Add date into draft using the 'Promote draft to post' command
    - Small updates to .gitignore
- Fix #32
    - Address small issue for ST2 when creating posts from an empty view

## v2.2.2 (2015-03-03)

- Fix #30
- Add support for opening posts/drafts in subdirectories
- Add support for promoting drafts to posts while maintaining directory tree

## v2.2.1 (2015-02-08)

- Closes PR #27
- Add support for finding Jekyll folders in active view
    - Enable in user or project settings
    - Will attempt to recursively find the `_posts` and `_drafts` directories
    - Falls back to project settings if none are found

## v2.1.3 (2015-01-28)

- Close #25
- Fix ST2 bug with format strings (related to Python 2.6)

## v2.1.2 (2015-01-18)

- Close #24
- Remove date/datetime keybindings that clash with ST defaults

## v2.1.2 (2014-12-17)

- Close #23
- Add support for multi-level dictionary in front-matter defaults
- Update JekyllPostFrontmatterCommand to use insert_snippet

## v2.1.0 (2014-12-07)

- Implement new post front-matter extras (Close #22)
- Allow for default post keys to be hidden using `null`
- Update default Jekyll settings file to include instructions
- Small changes to README

## v2.0.8 (2014-11-30)

- Fixes #14 with messages directory naming convention (only affects Linux systems)

## v2.0.7

- Merge pull request #18 from calledT/master

## v2.0.6 (2014-11-01)

- Merge pull request #17 from @fk128
- Fix duplicates from showing in Quick Panel
- Add directory check (in cases where drafts/posts paths do not exist)
- Add sorting of posts by last modified date

## v2.0.5 (2014-10-16)

- Fix ST2 specific bug in run_commands and set_timeout

## v2.0.4 (2014-09-04)

- Fix issue with trailing commas in commands

## v2.0.3 (2014-07-31)

- Small changes to default settings and front-matter snippet
- Add screenshot for new github.io project site page
- Add support for install and update messages
- Small updates to README.md

## v2.0.2 (2014-07-04)

- Add support for converting drafts to posts (Close #11)
- Small updates to README.md
- Small bug fixes to "open" commands

## v2.0.1 (2014-06-18)

- Fix #7
- Fix #9
- Add support for ST2 (Close #8)
- Add default keymaps back

## v2.0.0 (2014-06-16)

- Add Jekyll 2.0 snippets and completions
- Add brand new commands for post interaction
- Clean up code in most files for easier reading
- Remove default keybindings

## v1.0.1 (2014-01-17)

- Add documentation for configuring a Jekyll build system
- Small updates to `README.md` and `Main.sublime-menu`

## v1.0.0 (2014-01-12)

- Add platform specific key bindings to menu (previously missing)
- Add Textile (Jekyll) syntax file, and Update snippets/completions scope
- Add Textile comments and syntax specific preferences
- Add text.textile file to Tests directory
- Bumping version officially to v1.0.0

## v0.1.2 (2014-01-05)

- Fix #2 (updates to snippets)

## v0.1.1 (2014-01-04)

- Update `insert_date` command to support multiple formats
- Update syntax settings in all snippet files
- Update snippets
- Update `README.md` documentation
- Add keymap files

## v0.1.0 (2014-01-04)

- Initial commit
